{
  "texts": [
    "Or a researcher might try to use each financial news headline r to predict the company's realized return Y r in some event window after the headline's publication date.",
    "The second is an estimation problem -estimate some parameter that relates the economic concept V r to the linked variables (Y r,W r).",
    "For example, if each Congressional bill's brief text description r expresses the policy topic V r of the bill, such as whether it is related to defense, foreign affairs, or health, that topic could be related in a regression to the party affiliation or ideological voting score of the bill's sponsor W r.",
    "Or if each financial news headline r expresses positive or negative news about some company's future V r, that could be the outcome in a regression against past fundamentals W r or the explanatory variable in a regression against future returns.",
    "This is where LLMs come in."
  ]
}